
Overview of verb wait

The verb wait has 4 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (100) wait -- (stay in one place and anticipate or expect something; "I had to wait on line for an hour to get the tickets")
2. (49) wait, hold off, hold back -- (wait before acting; "the scientists held off announcing their results until they repeated the experiment")
3. (33) expect, look, await, wait -- (look forward to the probable occurrence of; "We were expecting a visit from our relatives"; "She is looking to a promotion"; "he is waiting to be drafted")
4. (2) wait, waitress -- (serve as a waiter or waitress in a restaurant; "I'm waiting on tables at Maxim's")
